  "texts": [
    "Built with advanced machine learning (ML) techniques, these tools now play a critical role in directing our attention in digital environments to the products we buy, the entertainment we consume, the news we read, and even the jobs we work, the homes where we live, and the people with whom we interact.",
    "Indeed, the information saturation of the digital world has made recommender systems not just useful but necessary for effective agency.",
    "These tools, and the sociotechnical systems in which they're embedded, therefore raise pressing moral concerns about how we now allocate our attention.",
    "On the one hand, they enable us to access an unprecedented amount of information with ease, potentially augmenting our agency in morally significant ways.",
    "For instance, they can direct us to far more information of personal, social, and political importance than we would be exposed to without them."
  ],
